The paper addresses a problem in machine learning related to image classification, specifically zero-shot learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with feature vectors extracted from images, which is a common topic in Computer Vision (cs.CV). The use of attribute vectors to describe objects and scenes suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates its algorithm on several datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) or Multimedia (cs.MM). Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.AI, followed by cs.CL and cs.MM.
